{
  "texts": [
    "Participants who failed at least one of three attention checks were excluded from the analyses (n = 8).",
    "The 192 participants in the final sample were 36.7 ± 13.0 (mean ± std) years old and 49% of them identified as female.",
    "Participants were shown a series of AI-generated persuasive messages about the various topics, which were tailored to the respective psychological profile: Nike sneakers (Big Five traits), exercise (regulatory focus), and climate action (moral foundations).",
    "As in Study 1, the prompts for these messages were minimal (e.g., Prevention focus: \"Write a short persuasive ad to convince a prevention-focused person to exercise more.",
    "\"; Fairness: \"Write a short political ad in favor of taking climate action that is tailored to people scoring high on the moral foundation of fairness\")."
  ]
}